{"id":42794,"date":"2025-03-08T15:33:39","date_gmt":"2025-03-08T11:33:39","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=42794"},"modified":"2025-03-08T15:33:39","modified_gmt":"2025-03-08T11:33:39","slug":"abu-bakr-keeps-promise","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/03\/08\/abu-bakr-keeps-promise\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Promises: Abu Bakr keeps the Prophet\u2019s pledge"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>If the goods come from Bahrain, I will give you such and such amount<\/strong>.\u201d The goods from Bahrain did not arrive until after the Prophet passed away. When the goods arrived, Abu Bakr ordered an announcement, \u201cWhoever has a promise or a debt from the Prophet, let him come to us and we will give it to him.\u201d I said, \u201cIndeed, the Prophet told me I could have such and such amount.\u201d Abu Bakr gave me a handful of coins and I counted it as five hundred. Abu Bakr said, \u201cTake twice what you have been promised.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1470, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1042<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/em><\/strong> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0648\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u062f\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u